Method

Step 1: Normalization

Let \(G\) denote the genotype matrix, and \(\tilde{G}\) the normalized genotype matrix such that for SNP \(i\) and individual \(j\):

\[\tilde{G}_{ij} = \frac{G_{ij} - f_i}{\sqrt{2 f_i (1 - f_i)}}\] where \(f_i\) represents the minor allele frequency of SNP \(i\).

Step 2: PCA

\[\tilde{G} = U \Sigma V^T\]
